{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"02884983-2839-4754-a0b3-1804312c9d43","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload)\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose name contains that string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. You can also filter by just the method name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"428b8648-92a0-47e3-b639-333f7631e1a1","outputTokens":162},"id":"0f0c7f7d-3ddf-4e5d-9e05-e71aa5bb051d","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:49:10.254Z","parentId":"6254eac9-e538-4e10-a097-2f824be632f8"}
